Police have launched a manhunt for al Shabaab militants who ambushed a school in Mandera and killed two teachers. The terrorists stormed Arabia Boys Secondary School in ManderaÂ on Wednesday at about 1 am and hurled an explosive device at the teachers' quarters. Two teachers, who were in the house perished in the fire. Police reservists who were guarding the school engaged the attackers who then fled. The reservists called for reinforcement. "All other teachers and students are safe. The hunt for the attackers is ongoing," the police said in a tweet. Area MCA Abdiaziz Dakat says the militants raided the school at dawn. The school is situated on the Kenya-Somalia border. Click here for the latest political news.